Package com.clientwallet.service

Class WalletService

java.lang.Object
com.clientwallet.service.WalletService
@Service public class WalletService extends Object
WalletService is a service class that provides various wallet-related operations. It interacts with the WalletRepository and TransactionRepository to perform operations such as creating a wallet, depositing, withdrawing, transferring funds, and fetching transaction history.

This service ensures that the operations are executed with the appropriate business logic and validations. All state-changing operations (deposit, withdraw, transfer) are handled within transactions to ensure consistency.

    • create

      public Wallet create(WalletCreateRequest request)
      Creates a new wallet.

      This method checks if a wallet with the same name already exists. If not, it creates and saves a new wallet.

      Parameters:
      request - The request object containing the wallet creation data.
      Returns:
      The created Wallet object.
      Throws:
      WalletCreateWalletWithNameAlreadyExistsException - If a wallet with the same name already exists.

    • get

      public Wallet get(UUID walletId)
      Retrieves a wallet by its unique ID.

      If the wallet with the given ID does not exist, a WalletNotFoundException is thrown.

      Parameters:
      walletId - The ID of the wallet to be fetched.
      Returns:
      The Wallet object if found.
      Throws:
      WalletNotFoundException - If no wallet is found with the provided ID.

    • deposit

      public Transaction deposit(WalletDepositRequest request)
      Deposits money into the specified wallet.

      The deposit operation checks that the currency of the request matches the wallet's currency. A WalletDepositCurrencyMissMatchException is thrown if the currencies do not match. If the deposit is successful, the transaction is saved with the status TransactionStatus.COMPLETED. In case of failure, the transaction status is set to TransactionStatus.FAILED.

      Parameters:
      request - The request object containing the deposit data.
      Returns:
      The Transaction object representing the deposit.
      Throws:
      WalletNotFoundException - If the wallet does not exist.
      WalletDepositCurrencyMissMatchException - If the currencies do not match.
      WalletDepositFailedException - If the deposit fails.

    • withdraw

      public Transaction withdraw(WalletWithdrawRequest request)
      Withdraws money from the specified wallet.

      The withdrawal operation checks that the wallet's currency matches the requested currency. It also checks that the wallet has enough balance to complete the withdrawal. If the withdrawal fails, the transaction status is set to TransactionStatus.FAILED.

      Parameters:
      request - The request object containing the withdrawal data.
      Returns:
      The Transaction object representing the withdrawal.
      Throws:
      WalletNotFoundException - If the wallet does not exist.
      WalletWithdrawCurrencyMissMatchException - If the currencies do not match.
      WalletWithdrawNotEnoughFundsException - If the wallet has insufficient funds.
      WalletWithdrawFailedException - If the withdrawal fails.

    • transfer

      public Transaction transfer(WalletTransferRequest request)
      Transfers money between two wallets.

      This method checks that the sender and receiver wallets are different, and that both wallets have the same currency as the request. The transfer operation also ensures that the sender wallet has sufficient funds for the transfer. If the transfer fails, the transaction status is set to TransactionStatus.FAILED.

      Parameters:
      request - The request object containing the transfer data.
      Returns:
      The Transaction object representing the transfer.
      Throws:
      WalletTransferSameWalletException - If the sender and receiver wallets are the same.
      WalletNotFoundException - If either the sender or receiver wallet does not exist.
      WalletTransferCurrencyMissMatchException - If the currencies do not match.
      WalletTransferNotEnoughFundsException - If the sender wallet has insufficient funds.
      WalletTransferFailedException - If the transfer fails.
